The paper focuses on the design of a simulation system for the management of UAVs, which involves human-in-the-loop control and explainability. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of Belief-Desire-Intention agents and the focus on critical scenarios suggest that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed human-computer interaction study suggests that the paper may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
